{
    "elem.1.37": {
        "id": "elem.1.37",
        "n": 37,
        "type": "proposition",
        "enunciation": "Triangles which are on the same base and in the same parallels are equal to one another.",
        "proof": [
            {
                "text": "Let `ABC`, `DBC` be triangles on the same base `BC` and in the same parallels `AD`, `BC`; I say that the triangle `ABC` is equal to the triangle `DBC`.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABC",
                    "DBC",
                    "BC",
                    "AD",
                    "BC",
                    "ABC",
                    "DBC"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let `AD` be produced in both directions to `E`, `F`; through `B` let `BE` be drawn parallel to `CA`, [elem.1.31] and through `C` let `CF` be drawn parallel to `BD`. [elem.1.31]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.31",
                    "elem.1.31"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "AD",
                    "E",
                    "F",
                    "B",
                    "BE",
                    "CA",
                    "C",
                    "CF",
                    "BD"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then each of the figures `EBCA`, `DBCF` is a parallelogram; and they are equal,",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "EBCA",
                    "DBCF"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "for they are on the same base `BC` and in the same parallels `BC`, `EF`. [elem.1.35]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.35"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "BC",
                    "BC",
                    "EF"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover the triangle `ABC` is half of the parallelogram `EBCA`; for the diameter `AB` bisects it. [elem.1.34]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.34"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABC",
                    "EBCA",
                    "AB"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the triangle `DBC` is half of the parallelogram `DBCF`; for the diameter `DC` bisects it. [elem.1.34]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.34"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "DBC",
                    "DBCF",
                    "DC"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "[But the halves of equal things are equal to one another.]",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the triangle `ABC` is equal to the triangle `DBC`.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABC",
                    "DBC"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore etc.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": []
            }
        ]
    }
}